No. 1795. State v. Thompson.

November Term, 1885.

January 25, 1886. W. J- Whipper, for the motion. J. B. Jloxoe, acting solicitor, contra.

Opinion

PER CüRiAM,

This was a motion to restore to the docket an appeal which had been, on motion, previously dismissed by the court. The court, following the decision in Clark Brothers v. Wimberly (ante, p. 188), held that the matter was res adjudicata.
